code: import os import pydicom import numpy as np import pandas as pd from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split import torch import torch.nn as nn import torch.optim as optim import torch.nn.functional as F from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader from torchvision import transforms from torchvision.models import efficientnet_b0 from tqdm import tqdm # Config IMG_SIZE = 224 N_SLICES = 32 BATCH_SIZE = 16 EPOCHS = 10 LR = 1e-4 WEIGHTS = [1.0] * 7 + [2.0] FOCAL_ALPHA = 0.25 FOCAL_GAMMA = 2.0 # Focal Loss with weighting class WeightedFocalLoss(nn.Module): def __init__(self, alpha=FOCAL_ALPHA, gamma=FOCAL_GAMMA, weight=WEIGHTS): super().__init__() self.alpha = alpha self.gamma = gamma self.weight = torch.tensor(weight) def forward(self, inputs, targets): BCE_loss = F.binary_cross_entropy_with_logits( inputs, targets, reduction="none", weight=self.weight.to(inputs.device) ) pt = torch.exp(-BCE_loss) focal_loss = self.alpha * (1 - pt) ** self.gamma * BCE_loss return focal_loss.mean() # DICOM preprocessing def load_dicom(path): dicom = pydicom.dcmread(path) data = dicom.pixel_array.astype(np.float32) return data * dicom.RescaleSlope + dicom.RescaleIntercept def apply_window(img, center=400, width=1800): img = np.clip(img, center - width // 2, center + width // 2) return (img - (center - width // 2)) / width class CervicalDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, df, root_dir, mode="train"): self.studies = df["StudyInstanceUID"].unique() self.labels = df.set_index("StudyInstanceUID") self.root_dir = root_dir self.mode = mode if mode == "train": self.transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Resize((IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE)), transforms.RandomAffine(degrees=10, translate=(0.1, 0.1)), transforms.ColorJitter(brightness=0.1, contrast=0.1), transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485], std=[0.229]), ] ) else: self.transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Resize((IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE)), transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485], std=[0.229]), ] ) def __len__(self): return len(self.studies) def __getitem__(self, idx): study_id = self.studies[idx] study_path = os.path.join(self.root_dir, study_id) slices = sorted(os.listdir(study_path), key=lambda x: int(x.split(".")[0])) # Select middle slices if len(slices) > N_SLICES: start = (len(slices) - N_SLICES) // 2 selected_slices = slices[start : start + N_SLICES] else: selected_slices = slices images = [] for fn in selected_slices: img = load_dicom(os.path.join(study_path, fn)) img = apply_window(img) img = self.transform(img).repeat(3, 1, 1) # RGB images.append(img) # Pad if needed if len(images) < N_SLICES: images += [torch.zeros_like(images[0])] * (N_SLICES - len(images)) stack = torch.stack(images) if self.mode == "train": labels = self.labels.loc[study_id][ ["C1", "C2", "C3", "C4", "C5", "C6", "C7", "patient_overall"] ].values return stack, torch.FloatTensor(labels) return stack, study_id class SpineModel(nn.Module): def __init__(self): super().__init__() self.backbone = efficientnet_b0(pretrained=True) self.backbone.classifier = nn.Identity() self.transformer = nn.TransformerEncoder( nn.TransformerEncoderLayer(d_model=1280, nhead=8), num_layers=2 ) self.heads = nn.ModuleList([nn.Linear(1280, 1) for _ in range(8)]) def forward(self, x): batch_size = x.size(0) features = [self.backbone(x[:, i]) for i in range(N_SLICES)] features = torch.stack(features) features = self.transformer(features) pooled = features.mean(dim=0) return torch.cat([head(pooled) for head in self.heads], dim=1) # Data prep df = pd.read_csv("./input/train.csv") train_ids, val_ids = train_test_split( df["StudyInstanceUID"], test_size=0.2, random_state=42 ) train_df, val_df = ( df[df.StudyInstanceUID.isin(train_ids)], df[df.StudyInstanceUID.isin(val_ids)], ) train_ds = CervicalDataset(train_df, "./input/train_images", "train") val_ds = CervicalDataset(val_df, "./input/train_images") train_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True, num_workers=4) val_loader = DataLoader(val_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, num_workers=4) # Model setup device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu") model = SpineModel().to(device) criterion = WeightedFocalLoss() optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=LR) # Training loop best_val_loss = float("inf") for epoch in range(EPOCHS): model.train() train_loss = 0 for inputs, labels in tqdm(train_loader, desc=f"Epoch {epoch+1}"): inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device) optimizer.zero_grad() outputs = model(inputs) loss = criterion(outputs, labels) loss.backward() optimizer.step() train_loss += loss.item() * inputs.size(0) train_loss /= len(train_ds) model.eval() val_loss = 0 with torch.no_grad(): for inputs, labels in val_loader: inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device) outputs = model(inputs) val_loss += criterion(outputs, labels).item() * inputs.size(0) val_loss /= len(val_ds) print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}: Train Loss {train_loss:.4f}, Val Loss {val_loss:.4f}") if val_loss < best_val_loss: best_val_loss = val_loss torch.save(model.state_dict(), "./working/best_model.pth") print(f"Best Validation Loss: {best_val_loss:.4f}") # Generate submission test_df = pd.read_csv("./input/test.csv") test_studies = test_df["StudyInstanceUID"].unique() test_ds = CervicalDataset( pd.DataFrame({"StudyInstanceUID": test_studies}), "./input/test_images", "test" ) test_loader = DataLoader(test_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, num_workers=4) model.load_state_dict(torch.load("./working/best_model.pth")) model.eval() preds = [] study_ids = [] with torch.no_grad(): for batch, sids in tqdm(test_loader): outputs = torch.sigmoid(model(batch.to(device))).cpu().numpy() preds.extend(outputs) study_ids.extend(sids) submission = [] for sid, pred in zip(study_ids, preds): for i, loc in enumerate( ["C1", "C2", "C3", "C4", "C5", "C6", "C7", "patient_overall"] ): submission.append({"row_id": f"{sid}_{loc}", "fractured": pred[i]}) pd.DataFrame(submission).to_csv("./submission/submission.csv", index=False)
